title: For Sale:  NIB DoubleStar Dissapator AR 5.56
postcontent:
PRIVATE PARTY: Flat top upper, full length handguard, chrome lined barrel, built by DoubleStar factory.  Still in the plastic and cardboard.  Comes with manual(s) and one 30 magazine.

Why a Dissapator? The long smooth handrail allows the shooter to slide the support hand forward for longer shots (accuracy).  The front sight is further forward and this creates a longer sight radius, making it a faster pointer with a better sight picture (accuracy).  When resting on cover, the handrail can be pushed/pulled further for more options on the improvised rest (accuracy).  Dissapator is the way to go.

Retail on this is $1,100.  This AR is on a completely different level than the DPMS puppy mill rifles, for example.  You can buy a DPMS (or equivalent quality) off the shelf now for about $650.  There is a quality difference.  DoubleStar makes their own barrels and other functionally critical parts in their own factory.  Additionally, DS has an incredible customer service policy.  They are 100% behind their rifles.  The accuracy and function of DS rifles compared to low end rifles is notable.  You get what you pay for and that is the difference.  For illustration, type in "DPMS AR" on a gun sale search.  See the going price.  Then type in "DoubleStar AR" and see the value difference.

I am a serious AR shooter, so if you have any questions about function or features... let me know.  The attached picture is an example/stock photo that gives you the idea of the dimensions/features.  Visit star15.com for actual specifications.

Must be 18 years old and will physically hand the box and rifle to you.  I am willing to ship it via FFL for a fee of $50.  I know a local FFL.

title: For Sale:  Destroyer Carbine (9x22mm)
postcontent:
The Destroyer Carbine is a small bolt action carbine usually chambered for the 9 x 23 mm Largo cartridge. It was used by Spanish police and prison services, including the Guardia Civil from the mid-1930s until the late 1960s, replacing the El Tigre Rifle.

It is essentially a scaled down Model 1893 Mauser with two rear-mounted locking lugs and a Mauser-style two-position flip safety. The Destroyer fired the same ammunition as the standard-issue police handgun but took the a different

 magazine, a 5-shot single stack and the longer rifle barrel resulted in greater muzzle velocity and accuracy, and subsequently range. It continued the tradition, started in the 1890s, of issuing police units with a short, handy, repeating carbine in pistol ammunition calibre.

title: For Sale:  DPMS Fully Built AR-10--HUGE Upgrades!! MINT Condition!
postcontent:
I built this LR-308 up as a trophy gun and it's got less than 100 rounds total through it and is in immaculate condition.

Includes a $700 NIKON M-308 4-16x42 Scope that's made specifically for the .308 platform with an incredible 95% light transmission rate.  It's fully waterproof, fogproof and shock proof and holds zero perfectly.

I also added a very expensive Magpul PRS Precision Tactical Sniper Stock which is an absolute necessity in a gun of this build.  I further complimented it with an aluminum monopod made specfically for the PRS that in combination with the Harris Bipod allows the gun stand to be integrated into the gun for ultra precise long range targeting.

I didn't stop there and added a precision machined bolt-on Kahntrol Solutions Heavy Muzzle Brake designed for the .308 round.  A bolt on brake is the best option since some states like California have made some threaded brakes illegal without a stamp.  You can simply unbolt and remove this from the bull barrell.  This muzzle brake along with the heavy bull barrel makes this AR-10 recoil lighter than most AR-15's.

Also added a tactical rubber coated grip with hand relief perch.  Excellent comfort and trigger control.

This is a beast of a gun and in one of the pictures you can see the size difference between it and an AR-15 sized HK 415 I have chabbered in .22.  This AR-10 get's a lot attention anywhere I've taken it including a couple of trips to the range.

Includes 3 steel magazines and about 20 rounds.

title: For Sale:  Trauma preps
postcontent:
Are you prepared? Sure you have your Defensive Tools, Ammo, Food Storage and BOB/GHB, but what does your First aid kit look like? Are you prepared to treat arterial bleeding? Do you have the supplies to treat a chest puncture or severed or mangled limb? In the times we live in we never know what we could potentially encounter. Get prepared and be ready. 

For Sale are 
20 x C.A.T (combat application tourniquet) 
20 x HyFin chest seals (for sucking chest wounds resulting from penetration of the upper thoracic cavity)
30 x QuickClot Combat Gauze.

Looking for $10 each piece with a minimum of 10 pieces. I will accept a USPS or Moneygram Money order. I will ship by standard USPS.

Now yes I know that the expiration date on QC Gauze is 6/14, but I called the guys at 
Z-Medica Corporation and they explained that the active ingredient is inorganic and except for it being very hydroscopic is relatively inert. Nothing to age out. Other than the packaging which with prolonged exposure to UV light and or constant molesting could damage it. The contents will last 10 years or better. The FDA requires an expiration date on ALL medical devices, medicines and supplies. And thinking about it, it also helps the manufacturers bottom line.... Making money. Now you can buy from the source and have a warm fuzzy feeling for $35-45 apiece or be smart and buy from me. 

Do your research and see what others are selling for. 
I will discount price for someone who wants it all. I am from Tulsa but currently live in North Carolina.
